.TH "port_r_mib_cnt" 9 "port_r_mib_cnt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
port_r_mib_cnt \- read MIB counter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" port_r_mib_cnt
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "int port "  ","
.BI "u16 addr "  ","
.BI "u64 *cnt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "port" 12
The port index.
.IP "addr" 12
The address of the counter.
.IP "cnt" 12
Buffer to store the counter.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine reads a MIB counter of the port.
Hardware interrupts are disabled to minimize corruption of read data.
